Really it was a great experience.

featured_reviews.review_id: "Jamia Masjid is built by Tipu Sultan near the Bangalore Gate in the eastern part of the fort in 1787 AD, this Mosque was used regularly for worship by him...The panoramic view of the area from the top is splendid... The building is an interesting example of the combination of Hindu and Islamic Architecture." - this is written on the Name plate of this mosque. When I reached there it was twilight and this yellow building seemed divine to me. The art and crafts of two minarets are majestic. Anyone can stop after seeing this extraordinary beautiful mosque on the side of the road.

Masjid is located in the route to Tippu Sultan's death place. No historical data about the masjid is displayed anywhere near to it.

This was the mosque where Tipu Sulthan use to come for prayer.

5 times Namaz is still there, and place of ablution is still maintained like in 1900s.

An office of the masjid is located near to the pond.

featured_reviews.review_id:
JAMA masjid or Masjid e Ala or jamia masjid is an historic mosque which consists of many age old historical walls,doors and abulation wells(which is now prohibited from using) as per rules and regulations of department of archaeology.

All the inscriptions inside the masjid are in persian letters which mostly translate about it build and the builder himself TIPU SULTAN.

The Namaz's are performed here till date and the timing of Jumma'h namaz is 1:45 with khutba starting from 1:15

All visitors are welcomed here but the prayer hall is prohibited to enter except muslims who come to pray inside.

Have fun about knowing its history
